review_reply.reply_text:
Dear Deeksha, I would like to address to your grievances one by one. First of all, the very first day of your consultation, the entire treatment plan was explained to you with their respective charges. Informed consent was taken from you before performing any procedure. You seemed to be very confused and anxious and that is why we had even asked you to come with your parents on the following appointments which you did not . I understand you had to wait in the reception area for 20 mins approx. but since on weekends there are lots of patients seeking appointments, we also expect a little patience from you. We have not suggested extraction for your upper tooth but only a filling. Extraction of upper teeth was suggested by some other clinic that you had visited to recheck on our treatments. Confusion happens when you visit multiple clinics and  get multiple suggestions, the result being nothing but increased confusions. Good to see that you have nowhere mentioned regarding the unimpaired healing that you had after undergoing a bony impaction surgery. Nowhere you had mentioned regarding the calls and messages that I have personally done to make sure that you are not having any discomfort after  surgery. 
Anyways, wish you good luck and good health.

survey_response.review_text:
TERRIFYING Experience.  The doctor doesn't give enough time to you. She is not upfront with the charges.You book appointment to get consultation from her, but some other assistant of her examines and reports to her. Then doctor listens to her and tells what to do. I went to see the doctor for tooth decay in the molar tooth, and asked her for a thorough examination of all teeth. I  waited for 45 min even though I had booked appointment. She hastily checked the tooth and asked for X-Ray to examine the tooth thoroughly. It was all fine till then. I was somewhat okay with her approach, and she seemed nice. After seeing the x-ray, she told she might have to extract the tooth and told the cost to be Rs 1000-2000. But after I got the tooth removed, I was asked to pay Rs 3500. WHY WAS I NOT INFORMED OF THE PRICE CHANGE EARLIER?? I felt deceived. I again went to see the doctor for a checkup few days after. WHY DID SOMEONE ELSE EXAMINED MY TEETH WHEN I HAD BOOKED AN APPOINTMENT TO CONSULT HER? Again her assistant examines the teeth, and tells that some other tooth has deep cavity and needs to be removed. WHY WAS A THOROUGH EXAMINATION OF ALL TEETH NOT DONE EARLIER?? That's it. I lost faith in her. Next day I went to see another famous doctor in Indiranagar. She examined the teeth thoroughly and told that I had a cavity in the tooth just above the one which was removed earlier. She told me that I should have got both teeth removed at the same time before only and suffered the pain only once. 

Would conclude by saying that the experience was really bad with Tooth Story Clinic and with Dr Madhumanti, as she could have done both surgeries together and I would have suffered less.

review_reply.reply_text: You had come to us for repeat  treatment of an infected Root Canal treated tooth done elsewhere. Re-RCT is an extremely critical and technique sensitive treatment.  The tooth had a broken needle piece inside the roots. We had completed 90% of the treatment in the first 2 sittings and then on the final 3rd sitting, if u suddenly do-not want to continue and ask for money refund, how we are supposed to do that ? Can you refund us the time, expertise , medicaments etc. used in the 2 sittings already done ?

survey_response.review_text:
I had an infection in the tooth on which RCT was done before. I had to undergo RCT again in order to clear the infection. The first two sittings were fine. I had a jaw pain (because of some surgery done 5 years ago). Due to this, I consulted my surgeon and he recommended to continue the RCT under his supervision. I couldn't continue my RCT treatment with doctor because of these complications. As I was helpless, I asked doctor to refund some of the amount from 4000 rs(which was taken at the start of the RCT). But the doctor refused to refund anything saying it's against their policies. I recommend people to think clearly before investing money here as in any case of emergency doctor won't refund anything. Even in big corporate hospitals money is taken per sitting / per treatment basis after treatment is done. And I believe in case of such emergencies they would also give it a thought about refund. 

Also, I had called in the morning and booked appointment at 6.30pm, which was pushed to 7.30 by the assistant at around 6pm because of busy schedule. Then for the 7.30 pm slot, I had to wait for half n hour again because of busy schedule. Then I had the above discussion with the doctor for which she said that we could have talked over phone (for such critical matter) and not wasted her 1 hour of slot. But I had also waited for half n hour which the doctor did not observe. 
Also, now after I have visited a dentist under the supervision of my surgeon says that the post in the tooth while doing the RCT is broken and thus the tooth cannot be saved as the post had become small and stuck in the root canal. Therefore, I have to now go for tooth extraction itself. 

Please be very sure of your case and then only visit the doctor.

Thank you.

My experience with Dr. Madhumanti has so far been extremely good. I had a couple of root canal treatments with her, followed by crown fitting. She is very patient *** **** *** ** *** *** ** **** *** ***** **** ** ********** She is a perfectionist and does not leave you with a half-baked job. In my case, the metal crown came with some defects. She tested this herself and got a new crown made. She is friendly, explains the issues clearly and seems very professional *** ******** I feel confident going to her for my treatments. She knows what she does and creates a warm friendly environment where she diligently treats patients by taking time and devotedly attending to them. She does not rush things up haphazardly to just cut short things and also does not come across as someone who'd fleece you for her benefit. I am glad with my treatment regimen with Dr. Madhumanti so far, and will continue to go to her for all my teeth related issues. Thanks a ton, doctor. And wish you all the best with your career as a dentist.

Dr. Madhumanti explains the issue in detail and I was very satisfied with the work. I got dental fillings done, and she got lots of X-Rays done to show me the cause of the issue clearly, and explain the process. Initially we thought there'd be 6 teeth affected and would require fillings, but during the filling process, the adjacent teeth were cleaned and it was found out that the decay is superficial and filling will not be required there. Doctor Madhumanti pointed it out and saved me the money. Highly recommended.

This was my second visit to The Tooth Story, Dr. Madhumanti's clinic. I needed 3 fillings to be done and a single sitting RCT for one tooth. It was my first RCT experience. Doctor was friendly as usual and took care of my problems within 2 days (checkup and treatment) as I was supposed to leave the city soon. She even agreed to come on her off day for the treatment. The RCT procedure was very smooth without any pain or discomfort, very unlike the experiences I have heard from my parents who have done their treatments elsewhere. Overall, I am satisfied and would highly recommend residents of Bangalore to visit The Tooth Story to solve their dental problems.

When I was just starting off on the chair, I heard a mum come in the clinic and proudly, gratefully and laughingly say to Dr. Madhumanti, "My daughter said to me to wait downstairs only". 

Dr. Madhumanti is extremely dexterous, was very verbal with communicating to me what she was going to do just before she was going to do it so that I would know what to anticipate. She continuously took feedback from my reactions and actively kept me engaged to understand how I was feeling throughout the process.

I've been going to a family dentist for years back at hometown, but I think I'm going to switch now.

Extremely recommend her to everybody.

Dear Mr.Raju, Thank you for your valuable feedback.
  If I recollect your appointment well, then I think I have explained thoroughly the entire procedure and its outcome before I started your treatment as I habitually do for my patients.To explain you even more, I drew a diagram of a tooth and had explained the extent of carious damage to your concerned tooth. I had given you the option of either a conservative or an invasive treatment method out of which you had chosen to go for the conservative method. Conservative method is only removal of infected  part while keeping the affected part of the carious dentin undisturbed and filling up the tooth as of now. It has been clearly mentioned to you that in future if the tooth gets symptomatic, you have to go for a root canal treatment. 
Before that day, you had come 3 times for the consultation and asked me the same questions. I had been very patient to answer your queries each time again and again and even now I will be happy to explain you for the 4th time as well. The rest I will leave on your comprehensive capability.
Good Luck.

The patient was Pregnant and was suffering from a lot of pain , we have examined the tooth and given two options of treatment - either extraction or RCT . 
If we go for extraction, she will lose the tooth which can be otherwise saved and moreover she has to take painkillers and antibiotics for 4-5 days and being in 1st Trimester, the Gynaecologist will definitely not recommend this.
Hence, RCT is a justified treatment option where I can relieve her pain without giving medicines as well save her chewing molar tooth. 
We even didn’t start any treatment as we asked to get a co - consent from her Gynaecologist as we will use local anaesthesia. 
 So, we just did a consultation and gave our suggestions.  If you cannot even take our suggestions, then donot come to doctors, do your treatment yourself.
